      "side": 1,
      "message": "Btw, one thing that could be simplified here is that I could simply return `true` instead of doing the `switch` + `#ifdef` thing, but that would work only if it\u0027s guaranteed that this function is called from outer `#ifdef` branches.\n\nIt _seems_ to hold across the codebase, e.g. `WP2GetCPUInfo(kSSE)` is always guarded by\n```\n#if defined(WP2_USE_SSE)\n    if (WP2GetCPUInfo(kSSE))\n#endif\n```\n\nbut I guess it\u0027s not, strictly speaking, guaranteed, so opted for a safer approach.",
      "revId": "ced02237512caf7e7bdf11b03c88eee183e635ce",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
