      "writtenOn": "2020-11-16T20:59:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the protection around WP2GetCPUInfo() is because we usually call SomeInitFunctionForSSE() right after:\n\nif (WP2GetCPUInfo(kSSE)) SomeInitFunctionForSSE();\n\nBy adding the #ifdef around, we don\u0027t need to defined SomeInitFunctionForSSE() as a void function in case WP2_USE_SSE is not defined, it simplifies the logic.\n\nSo, best to keep the #ifdef\u0027s in wasmCPUInfo().\nThat, we could default a \u0027return 0;\u0027 at line 205, and only handle the few \u0027return 1;\u0027 here and there when some #ifdef are defined...",
